  "prompt": "How much does it cost to hire a tax consultant to help me manage my stock option grant?",
  "response": "The cost of hiring a tax consultant to help manage your stock option grant can vary significantly based on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Experience and Expertise**: More experienced consultants or specialized firms may charge higher rates.\n2. **Location**: Fees can vary by geographic region, with consultants in major cities typically charging more.\n3. **Complexity of Your Situation**: If your stock option grant is part of a more complex financial situation (e.g., multiple income sources, investments, etc.), costs may be higher.\n4. **Fee Structure**: Some consultants charge hourly rates, which can range from $100 to $400 or more per hour, while others may offer flat fees for specific services\u2014this could be anywhere from a few hundred to several thousand dollars, depending on the scope of work.\n5. **Services Provided**: The extent of services (e.g., tax planning, compliance assistance, investment advice) will influence costs.\n\nOn average, you might expect to pay anywhere from $150 to $500 for an initial consultation, with ongoing advisory services potentially costing more. It's advisable to request quotes from multiple consultants and clarify what services are included to get a better idea of the total cost.",
